## 🚀 Getting Started

### 1) Prerequisites

Install required tools:

```bash
# Ubuntu / Debian
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y iverilog gtkwave yosys

# Optional (for SVG netlists)
npm install -g netlistsvg
```

For Sky130 technology mapping, install Sky130 PDK/liberty files in your machine.

### 2) Clone repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/hiagoairesd/hardwaredev.git
cd hardwaredev
```

### 3) Make scripts executable (first run only)

```bash
chmod +x setup.sh
chmod +x simu/simulate.sh
chmod +x synth/generic_synth.sh synth/specific_synth.sh synth/check_env.sh
```

---

## 🧪 Simulation

### Icarus flow (recommended)

```bash
cd simu
./simu_icarus.sh cpu_top
```

Run with test selector / runtime args:

```bash
./simu_icarus.sh cpu_top +test=1
./simu_icarus.sh cpu_top +test=4 +trace
./simu_icarus.sh cpu_top +test=4 +trace_w
```

For module-level tests (example):

```bash
./simu_icarus.sh alu
./simu_icarus.sh control_unit
./simu_icarus.sh registers_bank
```

### Waveforms

```bash
gtkwave simu/cpu_top.vcd &
```

