## ✅ Testing

### CPU Test Suite

The CPU testbench (`cpu_top_test.sv`) includes 15 comprehensive tests covering instruction types, memory operations, and edge cases:

|Test ID|            Name       |                 Description                   | Key Validation              |
|-------|-----------------------|-----------------------------------------------|-----------------------------|
| 1     | `regs`                | Basic register write operations               | R1=1, R2=2, R3=3            |
| 2     | `basic_swlw`          | Store/Load word integration                   | SW/LW addressing            |
| 3     | `border_swlw`         | Edge case signed immediates                   | Sign-extension, max memory  |
| 4     | `rtype`               | R-type ALU operations (ADD, SUB, AND, OR, XOR, SLT) | All ALU results       |
| 5     | `jump`                | Jump instruction control flow                 | J taken, PC update          |
| 6     | `beq`                 | Branch-if-equal and loop behavior             | BEQ taken/not-taken         |
| 7     | `andi`                | AND-immediate (zero-extension)                | RR operations, MEM writes   |
| 8     | `ori`                 | OR-immediate (zero-extension)                 | RR operations, MEM writes   |
| 9     | `lui`                 | Load upper immediate                               | Upper 16-bit placement |
| 10    | `sll`                 | Shift left logical                                 | Variable shift amounts |
| 11    | `srl`                 | Shift right logical                                | Variable shift amounts |
| 12    | `bne`                 | Branch-if-not-equal                                | BNE taken/not-taken    |
| 13    | `blt`                 | Branch-if-less-than (signed)                       | Signed comparison      |
| 14    | `fibonacci`           | Fibonacci sequence computation (fib(0) to fib(20)) | Loop control, arithmetic, MEM[0-19], fib(20)=4181 |
| 15    | `fibonacci_overflow` | Fibonacci with 32-bit overflow detection | Overflow at fib(47), wrapped value in MEM[32] |

### Quick CPU regression (Icarus)

```bash
for i in {1..15}; do
  echo "Running test $i"
  (cd simu && ./simu_icarus.sh cpu_top +test=$i) || echo "Test $i failed"
done
```

### Run individual CPU tests

```bash
cd simu

# Lightweight (PC/instr/opcode trace)
./simu_icarus.sh cpu_top +test=14 +trace

# Detailed (register writes, memory writes, branches, jumps)
./simu_icarus.sh cpu_top +test=15 +trace_w

# With waveform capture
./simu_icarus.sh cpu_top +test=4
```

### Focused unit runs

```bash
cd simu
./simu_icarus.sh alu
./simu_icarus.sh control_unit
./simu_icarus.sh registers_bank
./simu_icarus.sh fifo
```

